Staff members of Mercurius Commercial and representatives of Phuti Funeral Ministry Group gathered at the dealership in Polokwane last Thursday during the handing over of four brand new vehicles purchased by the funeral parlour group.
According to one of the Directors of Phuti Funeral Ministry Group, Mantsua Masenamela the parlour group is a big supporter of local dealerships when adding to their fleet regularly. Four brand new Mercedes-Benz Vito minivans were taken ownership of during the brief ceremony.
Mercurius Commercial Sales Manager Henry Venter thanked Phuti Funeral Ministry Group and its representatives for their continued support.
